locality: Huascarán National Park. 5 km below Cahuis Tunnel.

Huascarán National Park. Quebrada Pachachaca, a lateral valley of Quebrada Rurichinchay. Dense brushfields with some grassy or boggy areas; moderate to steep, E-facing slopes; soils of morainal material.
Huascarán National Park. Quebrada Shallap. Brushfields, including some small trees (Polylepis sericea & Buddleia incana); very large boulders; bottom and lower slopes.
Distrito Villa Rica, Comunidad Centro Bocaz, Zona de Amortiguamiento del Parque Yanachaga.
Huascarán National Park. Vinoyapampa, Quebrada Honda Moraines and valleysides.
Huascarán National Park. Quebrada Santa Cruz at base of and entering Quebrada Artizonraju. Shrubland at lower elevevation, and grassland above.
Entre Maria y Fortaleza Kuelap. Along road and in disturbed scrub.
